verbose_text: The detachment of cells with ethylenediamine tetraacetic acid (EDTA) also decreased the levels of integrins beta1 and alpha6 on the membrane, and ROCK inhibitor Y-27632 (treated for 10 min after detachment) further reduced the levels of integrins beta1 and alpha6 (XREF_FIG B, D).
evidence: levels of integrins beta1 and alpha6
